sequence: pHPHS319 was inserted at V5 Bxb1 landing pad

sequence: pHPHS524_pU6_sgRNAdropout_bGHpA_attB_Cas9-NLS-T2A-mCherry-T2A-Puro_SV40pA_KanR. Sequencing results: Dirty sequence data but based on the traces we can confirm 417P2 got in but no 417P3. It seemed to lose T7_promomoter-bGH_PA_terminator-attB-3xFLAG-SV40 NLS-Cas9-nucleoplasmin NLS-T2A-mCherry-T2A-Pure and it is connected to SV40-PA with a ~100bp nonspecific junction. This seems to have no attB sites and puro, so it will not affect transfection. Based on 30-40% contamination of this small unwanted plasmid in pHPHS524 we estimated the actual pHPHS524 has 180000-210000 colony variation. This is close to our bottleneck so we can directly use this plasmids.

pHPHS525_pU6_sgRNA_v3_Brunello_collision_NotI_20xWS_R1_T7_AscI_20xWS_KanR. NEB10-beta strain. 5-10x 10^6, less than 1% green colonies. Based on the restriction gel images, the re-tranformed pHPHS525 has some kind of contamination which showed ~1.2k band. This is bad so we will not use this.
First I will remove AscI site from the NMD reproters #199 and do mix/match with this old pHPHS525. Then add Cas9-Puro later.

pHPHS530_pU6_sgRNA_Brunello_collision_CUG_EYFP+2mCherry_20xWS_R1_T7_Cas9_puro_20xWS_KanR. NEB10-beta strain,  ~2x 10^6 is the estimated diversity. Gel purified: 70-80% parent contamination. pHPHS530 has the estimated 2x 10^6 diversity and 70-80% parent contamination. This high parent contamination is from that the parent plasmid (pHPHS528) includes the grandparent plasmid (pHPHS525) contamination because AscI cutting was not that good. For future use, we need to gel purify pHPHS528 to remove the grandparent contamination (pHPHS525). Then we can make better next step plasmids. Also we may want to use NotI or other cutitng site instead of AscI which has this uncut issue.
We decided to move forward by using pHPHS530.

The Gesicle Producer 293T Cell Line is a subclone of the transformed human embryonic kidney cell line, HEK 293, which is highly transfectable and supports high levels of protein expression. The cell line also constitutively expresses the simian virus 40 (SV40) large T antigen. Gesicles are produced in these cells via co-overexpression of packaging mix components, which include a nanovesicle-inducing glycoprotein and a protein that is displayed on the cell surface and mediates binding and fusion with the cellular membrane of target cells. Simultaneous overexpression of another protein cargo can result in incorporation of that protein within the gesicles. When combined with a gesicle production system, these cells are capable of producing high gesicle yields.

comment: The Gesicle Producer 293T Cell Line is a subclone of the transformed human embryonic kidney cell line, HEK 293, which is highly transfectable and supports high levels of protein expression. The cell line also constitutively expresses the simian virus 40 (SV40) large T antigen. Gesicles are produced in these cells via co-overexpression of packaging mix components, which include a nanovesicle-inducing glycoprotein and a protein that is displayed on the cell surface and mediates binding and fusion with the cellular membrane of target cells. Simultaneous overexpression of another protein cargo can result in incorporation of that protein within the gesicles. When combined with a gesicle production system, these cells are capable of producing high gesicle yields.

Stock received from Emily Hatch lab, then revived, expanded, and stocked by PN.

Cells are confirmed to be mycoplasma-free.

- 1 stock revived by PN for HP on 8/16/23
- 1 stock revived on 6/25/23. -PN

Final plasmid pAS247 has less than 10-20% contamination. 80-90% has correct size.
One nt (A) was added in the 5' end of sgRNA1: we didn't touch this for cloning but it has different sequences compared to pAS237 (CG added in the 5' end of sgRNA1 and C added in the 5' end of sgRNA2). So I think these errors of sgRNA1 and sgRNA2 are just sequencing artifacts.
One t added in between tracrRNA_v2 and pTet: This is a map error (pAS227/pAS237/pAS247 have the same error. The original plasmid pAS211-5 has correct sequences). I added one t to fix this for pAS227/pAS237/pAS247.
All setA/setB/setC have extra sequences in the ends of setA/B/C, can you check if these extra sequences are okay for our RELIC/MERFISH experiments?

Plasmidsaurus suggests that pAS249 looks correct, except for a 1-bp deletion just upstream of the cHS4_insulator adjacent to sgRNA Create optimal and deoptimal YFP / RFP AAVS1 targeting vectors #2. This is at the 5' end of the insert, so it seems like a possible consequence of Gibson assembly. I'm guessing it is unlikely to affect sgRNA structure or expression.
